        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What is local SEO and why does it matter?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">Local SEO (Search Engine Optimization) is the process of making sure your business appears prominently when people nearby search for what you sell. It covers Google Maps rankings, organic search results, and your Google Business Profile — the three places that drive foot traffic and phone calls for local businesses.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">Unlike paid ads that stop the moment you stop paying, good local SEO builds sustained visibility. A business that ranks well in Fort Pierce or Vero Beach keeps getting calls every day — without spending per click.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Google's local algorithm is built around three factors: relevance (do you offer what was searched?), distance (are you close enough?), and prominence (how well known and trusted is your business online?). We work all three.</p>
